🐳 Step 0: Requirements (Before You Start)

Make sure your system has:

✔️ Windows 10/11 (64-bit)
✔️ Virtualization enabled (in BIOS)
✔️ WSL 2 installed (for Windows users)
✔️ At least 4 GB RAM (8 GB recommended)
🔽 Step 1: Install Docker Desktop
Go to
👉 Docker Desktop official website
Download Docker Desktop for Windows
Install it (keep default settings)
During installation:
Enable WSL 2 integration when prompted
Restart your system after installation
▶️ Step 2: Start Docker & Verify
Open Docker Desktop
Wait until it shows “Docker is running”
Open Command Prompt / PowerShell and run:
docker --version

✅ Example output:

Docker version 25.x.x
📁 Step 3: Create Your Local Application
Create a folder:
myapp
Inside myapp, create file:
📄 app.py
print("Hello from Docker!")
📦 Step 4: Create Dockerfile

Inside the same myapp folder:

Create a file named exactly:

Dockerfile

⚠️ No .txt extension

Add this content:
FROM python:3.10
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
CMD ["python", "app.py"]
💡 Folder Structure Should Look Like:
myapp/
│
├── app.py
└── Dockerfile
⚙️ Step 5: Build Docker Image
Open terminal inside myapp folder

👉 (Right click → Open in Terminal / CMD)

Run:
docker build -t myapp .

🔹 What happens:

Docker reads the Dockerfile
Downloads Python image
Creates your custom image
🔍 Step 6: Verify Image

Run:

docker images

✅ You should see:

REPOSITORY   TAG       IMAGE ID
myapp        latest    xxxxxxxx
🚀 Step 7: Run the Container

Run:

docker run myapp

✅ Output:

Hello from Docker!
